@Entity(name="Role")

          requiredSqlCols="name")
@XmlElement(value="Role")
public class Role
extends GenericEntity
implements Entity

OO-Representation of the entity-relation Role

A role bundles a set of privileges i.e. permissions a user gains when having one or more roles. The right managment is not hierarchal, it is plain.

setName

public Role setName(String value)
Sets the value of name. If the new value is the same as the old value, this method has no effect, i.e. if you specify a new value, than isNameChanged() will return true. If you specify the same value as the old value isNameChanged() will return the same as it did before calling setName(...).

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the value is null (since name is not nullable)
